Final file:

```csharp
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;

namespace Compression;

internal static partial class NativeCompression
{
    [LibraryImport("compresslib", EntryPoint = "compress_buffer")]
    [UnmanagedCallConv(CallConvs = [typeof(System.Runtime.CompilerServices.CallConvCdecl)])]
    public static partial int CompressBuffer(
        [In] byte[] input,
        nuint inputLen,
        [Out] byte[] output,
        nuint outputLen,
        out nuint bytesWritten);
}
```

Key design choices:
- **`LibraryImport`** with source generation (requires `partial` class/method) — no runtime marshalling overhead.
- **`EntryPoint`** explicitly maps the C# PascalCase name to the C snake_case symbol.
- **`nuint`** is the correct .NET mapping for `size_t` (pointer-sized unsigned integer).
